red outstanding GOP and Owner’s return for the first time in 2025 since hotel re-branding in 2018.\n• Grew Loyalty Revenue Contribution to increase profit. Reached 37.2% (vs Goal of 25.1%)\n• Improved market share by 31.5% vs 2024\n• Ensuring a monthly review of the A&L to ensure a strong P&L\n\n3. Sales, Marketing & Business Development\n• Reviewing and discussing the commercial strategies on weekly basis with the Commercial team to grow market share.\n\n4. Guest Relations & Quality Control\n• Acting as a Brand Ambassador and empowering the Brand Champion to drive LQA Brand Audit\n• Supporting the Food Safety & Hygiene Champion to drive initiatives and actions to ensure the hotel is fully compliant and successfully passes the HACCAP Annual Audits.\n• Achieved 90.02% customer satisfaction in 2025 (from 86.5% in 2023 and 88.2% in 2024)\n• Sustainability and driving initiatives to improve energy saving, water saving, food waste reduction, plastic waste reduction, carbon footprint reduction…)\n\n5. Human Resources & Leadership\n• Driving a strong People Culture. Achieved 9.2 out of 10 in employee satisfaction in 2025 (+0.8 vs 2024).\n• Re-build the Commercial & Revenue Team to turn around the hotel performance\n\n6. Strategic Planning\n• Set a clear vision and strategy map around 3 pillars: People Culture, Brand Culture, Business Culture to set the hotel for success", "experiences/0/jobLocation": "Bangkok City, Thailand", "experiences/0/jobLocationCountry": "TH", "experiences/0/jobStartedOn": "4-2024", "experiences/0/jobStillWorking": "true", "experiences/0/logo": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D560BAQF4mKss-SDlhw/company-logo_400_400/B56ZoZR0xHHIAc-/0/1761360694907/movenpick_bdms_wellness_bangkok_logo?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=YWf-mYak3T1KyH32AMW4C3Z2WP_SIyDOcuFc6EM8_Ik", "experiences/0/title": "General Manager", "experiences/1/companyId": "484852", "experiences/1/companyIndustry": "Hospitality", "experiences/1/companyLink1": "https://www.linkedin.com/company/lebua